<h2>Dream Manager Application</h2><div>
<h3>What is a Dream Manager?</h3>
<p>A dream manager is a person you choose to help you accomplish/manage your dreams.<br>
   They are there to help you along your journey of accomplishing dreams.</p>
<h3>How do I request a Dream Manager?</h3>
<p>You request a dream manager by clicking on the Menu and selecting "request dream <br>
	manager". This will create a request and if the manager accepts it they will be <br>
	your dream manager. This means they can do everything that you can to your dreams<br>
	and tasks.</p>
<h3>How do I get a new Dream Manager?</h3>
<p>You can get a new dream manager by removing your current one from the menu<br>
	and then requesting a new one from the menu.</p>
<h3>How do I accept/reject a Dream Manager's claim on me?</h3>
<p>Open your menu and click accept or reject. There is also an email sent to you when<br>
	a dream manager claims you that has accept/reject links.</p>
</div>
<h2>Dreams</h2><div>
<h3>What is a Dream?</h3>
<p>A dream is something you wish to have, do, see, own, create, become. A dream can be<br>
	anything you want it to be. If you can describe it, it can be classified as a dream.</p>
<h3>How do I add a Dream?</h3>
<p>A dream can be added by clicking on the <g:img file="add.png" width="20" height="20" /> on the Your progress tab on the <br>
	dashboard. Fill out the form and click save. Then you can add another or click on <br>
	the minus sign to close the form.</p>
<h3>How do I delete a Dream?</h3>
<p>From the view screen you can click the delete button or the <g:img file="delete.png" width="20" height="20" />  in the search dream<br>
	tab on the dashboard. Be careful deleting things as there is no UNDO in the current <br>
	version of the software.</p>
<h3>How do I edit a Dream?</h3>
<p>From the dream in progress tab click on the dream and then click the <g:img file="skin/database_edit.png" width="20" heigth="20"/>, or from the <br>
	search dream view simply click on the Title, then click on <g:img file="skin/database_edit.png" width="20" heigth="20"/>.</p>
<h3>How do I mark a Dream complete?</h3>
<p>This will be done automatically when all dream tasks are 100% done.</p>
<h3>Who can see my Dreams?</h3>
<p>Only you and your dream manager.</p>
</div>
<h2>Tasks</h2>
<div>
<h3>What is a Task?</h3>
<p>A task is anything that upon being done will help further the accomplishment of <br>
	the dream it belongs to.</p>
<h3>How do I add a Task?</h3>
<p>Click on the <g:img file="add.png" width="20" height="20" /> next to "Dream tasks:" header on your short/long term lists,<br>
	or when editing a dream click on the <g:img file="add.png" width="20" height="20" />.</p>
<h3>How do I edit a Task?</h3>
<p>Click on the <g:img file="skin/database_edit.png" width="20" height="20" />.</p>
<h3>How do I delete a Task?</h3>
<p>Click on the <g:img file="delete.png" width="20" height="20" /> next to it in dream progress tab. Or View a dream from the search <br>
	page click on the dream, then click on the task name to view, then click delete.</p>
<h3>How do I mark a Task Complete?</h3>
<p>This is done by clicking on <g:img file="complete.jpg" width="20" height="20" /> inside the dream on the Dreamer Dashboard.</p>
<h3>Who can see my Tasks?</h3>
<p>Only you and your dream manager.</p>
</div>
